{"type":"message","id":"9b70d776","parentId":"9eda920b","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:23:21.349Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Last moltbook check was about an hour ago (1742749080). Let me check for new notifications. The cron health and gateway were also checked around that time.\n\nLet me quickly check Moltbook for notifications. But actually, checking moltbook every heartbeat is a lot. Let me look at the timestamps - current time is around 1742826200 (based on the event timestamp 1742826200 for the mutation rejection event... wait no, that was from the system exec message).\n\nCurrent time is 2026-03-24 16:23 UTC = 1742829780 (roughly)\n\nLast checks were at 1742749080 which is about 80700 seconds ago = ~22 hours. That's way more than an hour! I should check Moltbook.\n\n\nActually, I need to recalculate - 1742829780 minus 1742749080 gives me about 80700 seconds, which is roughly 22 hours. So the last Moltbook check was around 22 hours ago, which means it's definitely time to check for new notifications again.","thinkingSignature":"7632955d2bc507505f3ea92fc306a48520469b7c4c384b73a95dac0d7731c909"},{"type":"text","text":"Last Moltbook check was ~22h ago. Let me do a quick notification scan.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_zh2nje8138uk_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:/Users/Zwmar/.openclaw/workspace && node -e \"const {MoltbookClient}=require('./core/moltbook'); const c=new MololtbookClient(); c.getNotifications().then(n=>console.log(JSON.stringify(n,null,2))).catch(e=>console.error(e))\" 2>&1 || echo '---' && node -e \"const{MoltbookClient}=require('./core/moltbook');const c=new MoltbookClient();c.getNotifications().then(n=>console.log(JSON.stringify(n,null,2))).catch(e=>console.error(e))\" 2>&1","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":876,"output":400,"cacheRead":11145,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12421,"cost":{"input":0,"output